venue.name: Owl Village Harajuku (ふくろうの里 原宿店)

tip.text: Great udon, sat at the bar and had a full view of the cook making tempura. Entire restaurant Seats only 10 in total so no large groips
The wait is long but the food is as authentic as it can get, especially the Penang Assam Laksa. Love their dessert menu, I come here for their lesser known sweets like red ruby.

Riad was beautiful, built in the 10th century. However it is unsafe to be out after 8pm. Our voices carried in the open space so we were told to whisper in our rooms to be considerate of other guests.
The main attraction here is the airplanes that take off and land while you eat. My son was beside himself & it was the longest lunch we've had. Waiters were attentive & food was great
Service is on the slow side but the food is amazing. Come during lunch and order the lunch only specials called Thali (pictured) you get to sample a bit of everything.
Been to many fine restaurants (even to a Cordon Bleu one last night which is highly rated) and the food here is tops! I prefer it to last night's restaurant, the strawberry chicken salad was 👍🏻👍🏻
